Use ./run.sh to run the CPU-SWIFT example. This version reads the ./gresho.yml
parameter file.

Use ./runGPU.sh to run the GPU-SWIFT example. By default, this version reads
the ./greshoGPU256.yml file.

Other parameter files for differently sized examples are available:

- greshoGPU64.yml     64^3 ~= 262k  particles
- greshoGPU128.yml   128^3 ~= 2e6   particles     Uses a 64^3 initial box and replicates it 2 times in each dimension. Plotting script will plot horrible looking results if unmodified.
- greshoGPU256.yml   256^3 ~= 16e6  particles     Uses a 64^3 initial box and replicates it 4 times in each dimension. Plotting script will plot horrible looking results if unmodified.
- greshoGPU384.yml   384^3 ~= 57e6  particles     Uses a 64^3 initial box and replicates it 6 times in each dimension. Plotting script will plot horrible looking results if unmodified.
- greshoGPU512.yml   512^3 ~= 134e6 particles     Uses a 64^3 initial box and replicates it 8 times in each dimension. Plotting script will plot horrible looking results if unmodified.

